Package odase.annotations

Annotation types used in the Hedwig generated code to provide model details such as cardinality, and source URI.

See: Description

  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    SourceType.Type  
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Cardinality
    Methods generated from OWL files will have this annotation, which gives the cardinality restrictions of the corresponding property.
    IgnoreOnPartialWrite
    This annotation is added to pig-generated fields to state that this field should not be ignored, when using the PojoPartialWriter, meaning that the resulting object will have null in that field.
    NoInference
    This annotation is added to hedwig-generated query methods that don't do inference (i.e.
    OnlyInferred
    This annotation is added to hedwig-generated query methods that are only inferred (set does not make sense).
    PredicateCostWeights
    Engineering annotation
    PredicateCostWeights.PredicateCostWeight  
    RangeClass
    Hedwig generated getters and setters will get this annotation.
    RangeDatatype  
    RangeFacets
    Methods generated from OWL files for custom datatype properties will have this annotation, which gives the XSD facets for the custom datatype.
    SourceType
    Classes and methods generated from OWL files will have this annotation, which gives the URI of the corresponding OWL class or property.
    SourceURI
    Classes and methods generated from OWL files will have this annotation, which gives the URI of the corresponding OWL class or property.
    SubClasses  
    UnmappedRange
    This annotation is added to generated fields/methods correspond to an object property with a range that is outside the generation scope, and is thus unmapped.
